            <Field key="sec_vacancy"><Value>Senior Finance Analyst (interim for 6 months)

   Central Functions


    Colchester, Essex

   Salary Band 3 plus benefits
   Full Time
   Closing: 28/06/2019
   1 position available
   Job Reference No. 50161999

Job Specification

   Are you looking for an opportunity with a leading national business? If the answer is YES, Tarmac are recruiting in Cochester and this could be the ideal role for you.

   At Tarmac, our people have been shaping the world around us for more than 100 years, from the roads we drive on every day, to the buildings, airports, stadiums, offices and hospitals we live in and work in. We are very proud of our history and what makes us the company we are today. We also have huge ambitions for the future and want to continue our growth and innovation to remain at the leading edge of our industry We offer an extensive range of career development opportunities and industry-leading rewards. We're looking for people who share this passion, enthusiasm and collaborative approach to join our team of over 7,000 employees across the UK. As part of a global business in CRH, the career opportunities are limitless.

   Joining our team as a Senior Finance Analyst (interim for 6 months) you will be entitled to a highly competitive basic salary and a great range of benefits including:

   Bonus scheme
   Enhanced holiday entitlement
   Contributory pension scheme
   Access to the Tarmac Reward website with discounts on retailers, holidays, etc.
   Access to our Employee Assistance helpline for free and confidential advice.
   Training and development opportunities

   What are we looking for?

   Qualified / Part Qualified accountant to support the Materials South team for budgeting, forecasting, reporting and with analytical support to help drive improved insight into the results and performance of the Region.

   What will I be responsible for?

   To provide a regional support in the consolidation and management of monthly financial results and reporting for the region including preparation of core MI packs.
   To co-ordinate the regional business planning and reporting cycle (strategic plan, budgets, outlooks and forecasts) in line with Group reporting requirements.
   To support Head of Finance by providing finance reporting and analytics support in:
   - Preparation of regional 5 year strategic plan, budget and outlook presentations for the regional executive
   - Preparation of regional MI and benchmarking (functional area KPIs)
   - Reporting and reviewing regional support costs
   - Analytics support to the regional finance team for designated National Excellence Programmes e.g. Manufacturing and Asset Optimisation to ensure delivery of Regional targets.

   To be responsible for managing the regional Analyst team ensuring service level delivery to functional heads (S&amp;OP, Logistics, Commercial and Technical)
   To be responsible for providing the financial support and ad hoc support to HoF and AFMs
   To provide regional tracking and support regional challenge to the Areas on the delivery of excellence programme benefits in line with targets.

   If you feel you have the skills and experience required to excel in the role of Senior Finance Analyst, we want to hear from you. Please click APPLY below to register your interest!

   All applicants will be required to provide evidence that they have the right to live and work in the UK, as per the UK Illegal Working Immigration, Asylum and Nationality Act 2006 at the interview stage.

   No agencies please.

   Tarmac is an equal opportunities employer.
   Apply</Value></Field>
